class Solution {
    public int clumsy(int n) {
        if (n <= 2) return n;
        int result = n;
        n--;
        int count = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            if (count % 4 == 0) {
                result *= n;
            } else if (count % 4 == 1) {
                result /= n;
            } else if (count % 4 == 2) {
                result += n;
            } else {
                result -= n;
            }
            count++;
            n--;
        }
        return result;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution directly calculates the clumsy factorial by iterating from n down to 1, applying the operations in the specified order. It handles edge cases for n <= 2 and uses a counter to cycle through the operations. The main strength is its simplicity and efficiency.
